column18: Most of the courses in the department are definitely not designed for effective teaching. Most of the instructors fail to deliver the content properly. No one makes an effort to create a curriculum that aligns with current needs. The same courses with the same content have been taught for nearly 30 years. The assignments given are almost entirely useless. We barely have any opportunities to go on field trips. We absolutely do not learn how to think critically or question concepts. There are too many subjects and courses. All we try to do is score high on exams. We have no time to critically analyze any topic. When we ask questions to the instructors, most of them respond dismissively or condescendingly. All the courses remain superficial. Despite the average grades of a course consistently being low, the instructors continue to teach it the same way. I definitely don't feel like I'm receiving a quality education at METU. Since I need a diploma to practice my profession, I’m simply forcing myself to finish school somehow.
